## Testing Strategy

### Performance Testing
- **Load Testing**: 30 antibiotics baseline, 100+ future scalability
- **Memory Testing**: Extended clinical session simulation (4+ hours)
- **Mobile Testing**: Touch interface validation on clinical tablets
- **Accessibility Testing**: Screen reader and keyboard navigation validation

### Clinical Workflow Testing
- **Emergency Scenarios**: <30s access time validation
- **Network Resilience**: Offline mode functionality testing
- **Battery Impact**: Power consumption monitoring on clinical devices
- **Multi-session Testing**: Memory leak detection during long clinical shifts

## Success Criteria

### Technical Validation
- [ ] All Phase 3 performance targets met or exceeded
- [ ] Memory footprint <50MB during extended clinical sessions
- [ ] Mobile touch interface validated on clinical tablets
- [ ] Offline capability functional for network interruptions

### Clinical Validation  
- [ ] Emergency access <30s to any critical antibiotic information
- [ ] Touch targets ≥44px for clinical glove compatibility
- [ ] Battery optimization preserves clinical device power
- [ ] Accessibility validation passes WCAG 2.1 AA compliance

### Integration Validation
- [ ] Complete Phase 3 system integration with optimized performance
- [ ] Backward compatibility with Phase 2 Northwestern components
- [ ] Error recovery gracefully handles network failures and data corruption
- [ ] Clinical accessibility enhanced with screen reader optimization

